# note : in python variables are just labels that point to objects in memory. 
# When you assign a value to a variable, you are creating an object in memory and the variable points to that object. 
# also the object in the memory has a type and a value not label which is referencing it.
# also for garbage collection, when there are no more references to an object, it can be automatically cleaned up by the garbage collector. but integer and string objects are treated dierently and optimized not to immediately get cleaned up.